Consider a 4x5 rectangle grid where $2$ of the unit squares have been initially shaded. Determine the least number of additional unit squares that must be shaded so that the resulting figure has horizontal and vertical lines of symmetry.
{{DGM:7fb444ca7fe59277}}
$\textbf{(A) } 3 \quad \textbf{(B) } 4 \quad \textbf{(C) } 5 \quad \textbf{(D) } 6 \quad \textbf{(E) } 7$

The population of Canada in 1980 was approximately 24,343,181. The area of Canada is 3,855,103 square miles. Given there are $ (5280)^2 $ square feet in one square mile, which number below best approximates the average number of square feet per person?
{choices will be generated after solving}
$\textbf{(A)}\ 4,000,000\qquad \textbf{(B)}\ 5,000,000\qquad \textbf{(C)}\ 4,500,000\qquad \textbf{(D)}\ 4,400,000\qquad \textbf{(E)}\ 4,900,000$
